     </div>
    <div class="attribute-header">
        <h2>> <a href="http://ez.no/About-eZ/Events-News/News/Press-Release-eZ-Publish-Platform-5.1-Released" title="Press Release: eZ Publish Platform 5.1 Released">Press Release: eZ Publish Platform 5.1 Released</a></h2>
     </div>

    <div class="attribute-byline">
	    </div>

    

    <div class="attribute-body float-break">
      <p><i>Skien, Norway, May 28th, 2013</i></p><p>eZ Systems, the maker of the eZ Publish Platform, announced today the immediate availability of eZ Publish Platform 5.1. With this version, the second so far in the new 5.x series, eZ has consolidated the strategic direction of its product and service initiated in 2012. Developers will benefit from increased stability, performance and maturity whilst a range of new additions will add value for marketers and business users expanding from a pure content management need to digital experience management. The eZ Publish Platform offers an increasingly integrated set of solutions for organizations of all types to build compelling content-driven digital experiences to cover the whole Create Deliver Optimize content lifecycle management vision that eZ has set out to offer the market.</p><div class="separator"><span></span></div><a name="eztoc362365_1" id="eztoc362365_1"></a><h2>Combining the eZ Publish concept with a cutting edge web stack and full featured REST API for more agility, performance and interoperability.</h2>
<div class="object-left"><div class="content-view-embed">
	<div class="class-image">
		<div class="attribute-image">

	
															
		
		
																								
													
													
						
			<a href="http://ez.no/var/ezflow_site/storage/images/media/images/ez-publish-5.1-platform-evolution2/362586-1-eng-GB/eZ-Publish-5.1-Platform-Evolution_fancybox.png" rel="fancybox" class="fancybox"><img src="http://ez.no/var/ezflow_site/storage/images/media/images/ez-publish-5.1-platform-evolution2/362586-1-eng-GB/eZ-Publish-5.1-Platform-Evolution_listitem.png" width="130" height="80" style="border: 0px solid ;" alt="eZ Publish 5.1 Platform - Evolution" title="eZ Publish 5.1 Platform - Evolution" /><span title="Enlarge this image"></span></a>		
		
		
	</div>
			</div>
</div>
</div><p>eZ Publish Platform 5.0 generated a lot of enthusiasm and interest. With this new release, it takes the discussion to the next phase. While engineers worked on 5.1 they focused on making the software platform more solid, more mature, more scalable and much faster.</p><p>As with the preceding 5.0 version, 5.1 is also based on the dual kernel approach whereby the legacy system is used for the editorial user interfaces, the content repository and all the power of the full featured content management system; while the new stack adds on top a complete set of APIs (REST and PHP) as well as a brand new web framework based on Symfony2.</p><p>The highlights of the new benefits for developers are:</p>
<ul>

<li>The fastest eZ version ever thanks to the Symfony web framework and the improvements of Symfony 2.2</li>

</ul>

<ul>

<li>A redesigned cluster support for high traffic websites, which now makes it possible to run with the new kernel of the platform in a cluster setup as much as with the legacy version.</li>

<li>Improvement of the eZ Publish 5 REST API with new support for sessions and XSRF</li>

<li>A new data cache system that enables you to multiply performance of website when operating in dynamic mode</li>

<li>Full support for the multi-site management feature in the new web framework</li>

<li>The support in the new kernel for new field types including the rendering of eZ Flow landing pages</li>

<li>New completed demo sites, a cookbook, improved documentation and tutorials.</li>

</ul>
<p>For more information, a full list of the improvements, bug fixes and new features brought to the eZ Publish core platform is available in the <a href="http://ez.no/About-eZ/Blog/eZ-Publish-5.1-Platform-at-a-glance-Release-Notes" title="eZ Publish 5.1 Platform at a glance - Release Notes" target="_self">technical release notes</a>.</p><p>“eZ Publish version 5.0 represented a bold new direction for the platform that has brought a lot of great new abilities while still maintaining backward compatibility. Release 5.1 continues this by quickly maturing the new platform architecture and enabling even more Symfony-based eZ Publish projects.” said &nbsp;<a href="http://share.ez.no/community/profile/9901" title="Joe Kepley member of the eZ Publish Community" target="_blank">Joe Kepley</a> - <a href="http://ez.no/Partners/Find-a-Partner/Blend-Interactive" title="Blend Interactive" target="_self">Partner at Blend Interactive</a> , a USA eZ Systems partner.</p><div class="separator"><span></span></div><a name="eztoc362365_2" id="eztoc362365_2"></a><h2>A more integrated platform approach for business to build digital experience</h2><p>eZ has also been working on the components related to the customer experience management (CXM) side of the platform. Here, the focus is to provide a much more integrated platform, making it easy to combine the different pieces of the Digital Experience - the content and its platform at the core.</p>
<div class="object-right"><div class="content-view-embed">
	<div class="class-image">
		<div class="attribute-image">

	
															
		
		
																								
													
													
						
			<a href="http://ez.no/var/ezflow_site/storage/images/media/images/ez-publish-5.1-platform-the-platform-approach/362601-2-eng-GB/eZ-Publish-5.1-Platform-The-platform-approach_fancybox.png" rel="fancybox" class="fancybox"><img src="http://ez.no/var/ezflow_site/storage/images/media/images/ez-publish-5.1-platform-the-platform-approach/362601-2-eng-GB/eZ-Publish-5.1-Platform-The-platform-approach_listitem.png" width="130" height="80" style="border: 0px solid ;" alt="eZ Publish 5.1 Platform - The platform approach" title="eZ Publish 5.1 Platform - The platform approach" /><span title="Enlarge this image"></span></a>		
		
		
	</div>
			</div>
</div>
</div><p>This way, 5.1 brings a few significant steps forward:</p>
<ul>

<li>eZ Marketing Automation is improved, offering more integration to bridge content management and marketing automation such as advanced use of online marketing forms within the CMS, ability to run web nurturing campaigns or simply improved management of landing pages.</li>

<li>eZ Recommendation service has been significantly enhanced, facilitating the way web developers can configure the extension in their website and providing more accurate tracking capabilities.</li>

<li>eZ Liveviewer 2, the real-time analytics solution, was significantly updated with a new front page monitoring feature able to recommend editors which content to more efficiently promote. It has also been re-implemented fully in HTML5 and is now tablet compliant meaning you can monitor your live traffic and content trends on the go.</li>

</ul>
<p>eZ odoscope has also been fine tuned with tighter integration and performance enhancements.</p><a name="eztoc362365_3" id="eztoc362365_3"></a><h2>eZ Publish Cloud for better time to market and total cost of ownership</h2><p>With 5.1, the cloud deployment service is now integrated as a core component of the platform subscription itself. When a customer subscribes to the eZ Publish Platform today, they also get access to a cloud environment, ready for deployment as part of the service. Charges are then only incurred for the usage of the infrastructure. This is the eZ elastic way!</p><p>Not only will developers like it for the ease of use, but more importantly, their bosses and business owners will appreciate the combination of the radically reduced time to market for new projects to reach production, the reduced infrastructure cost and the pay-only-for-what-you-use model that puts them in greater power.</p><a name="eztoc362365_4" id="eztoc362365_4"></a><h2>eZ Publish dual kernel for smoother migration path and better sustainability</h2><p>While eZ Publish 5 includes a brand new architecture with many benefits, it also fully supports and relies on the old architecture which we call the “Legacy System”. The Legacy System remains a core component of the 5.x series. Existing eZ Publish users can benefit from version 5.1 at very low cost, and can be sure the “old way” of doing things is still possible. For instance, using the old templating system or older extensions. It is important to recognise that the adoption of the new components in eZ 5.x is not mandatory from day one, it can be a progressive build into the new technology.</p><p>“<i>As a software company we have to invest as much effort in developing new features as servicing our existing customer base and offering them true reliability and sustainability</i>” says Aleksander Farstad, CEO of eZ Systems.</p><p>“<i>While people often remember only new features, a lot of the success for our customers comes with our attention to remain predictable and to offer a sustainable development path. That is what we offer with 5.1: a very smooth and flexible migration path, a long term support plan and full backward compatibility with content and existing data.</i>”</p><p>To further demonstrate the commitment to sustainability, eZ Systems provides a full roadmap for the coming years, and welcomes contributions and feedback on the innovation process with an open development process. The goal is to ensure that existing users can understand, evaluate and decide upon their own project’s roadmap and even influence eZ’s software development roadmap itself!</p><a name="eztoc362365_5" id="eztoc362365_5"></a><h2>Availability</h2><p>eZ Publish 5.1 is available immediately, under a hybrid delivery model (in the cloud and for download as part of the same package). For more information on eZ Publish 5.1, eZ Publish roadmap and all related information please visit&nbsp;<a href="http://ez.no/Products/Introducing-eZ-Publish-Platform-5.1" target="_self">http://ez.no/Products/Introducing-eZ-Publish-Platform-5.1</a>.</p><a name="eztoc362365_6" id="eztoc362365_6"></a><h2>About eZ</h2><p>eZ Systems is the globally recognised commercial open source software provider. Our leading and innovative approach takes your enterprise platform beyond content management (CMS) into creating a true digital experience with systematic optimization capabilities. The eZ Publish platform sets new standards for digital lifecycle management, including recommendations and smart web analytics functionality, coupled with an application market place of certified extensions. Thousands of organizations worldwide benefit from optimized and intelligent multi-channel communications solutions. eZ's client base includes small, medium and large enterprises across all industries such as media, publishing and broadcasting, financial services, telecoms, retail, government, manufacturing, logistics, and education.</p><a name="eztoc362365_7" id="eztoc362365_7"></a><h2>Contact information</h2><p>Please get in touch at communications@ez.no</p>
    </div>

